## Beta Features & Server-Side Tools

**\`betas:\` is NOT a param on \`$client->messages->create()\`** \u2014 it only exists on the beta namespace. Use it for features that need an explicit opt-in header:

\`\`\`php
use Anthropic\\Beta\\Messages\\BetaRequestMCPServerURLDefinition;

$response = $client->beta->messages->create(
    model: '{{OPUS_ID}}',
    maxTokens: 16000,
    mcpServers: [
        BetaRequestMCPServerURLDefinition::with(
            name: 'my-server',
            url: 'https://example.com/mcp',
        ),
    ],
    betas: ['mcp-client-2025-11-20'],  // only valid on ->beta->messages
    messages: [['role' => 'user', 'content' => 'Use the MCP tools']],
);
\`\`\`

**Server-side tools** (bash, web_search, text_editor, code_execution) are GA and work on both paths \u2014 \`Anthropic\\Messages\\ToolBash20250124\` / \`WebSearchTool20260209\` / \`ToolTextEditor20250728\` / \`CodeExecutionTool20260120\` for non-beta, \`Anthropic\\Beta\\Messages\\BetaToolBash20250124\` / \`BetaWebSearchTool20260209\` / \`BetaToolTextEditor20250728\` / \`BetaCodeExecutionTool20260120\` for beta. No \`betas:\` header needed for these.

